    <div class="my-5">
        <h2>Forest Lawn and International Avenue</h2>
        <p class="par-lg">International Avenue is a vibrant and ethnically diverse culture and business hub situated on 17 Avenue SE in southeast Calgary. Known as the ‘mini United Nation’ of Calgary, the area is home to an eclectic mix of retail businesses from across the world, featuring some of the best of the world’s cuisines, services, industries and auto businesses. Spanning 35 blocks on 17 Avenue SE, International Avenue takes its visitors ‘around the world’ to enjoy a stunning mix of sounds, sights, foods and experiences.</p>
        <p class="par-lg">The Avenue is part of Forest Lawn, which is a former town and neighbourhood located in the southeast quadrant of Calgary in Alberta. The southern border of the neighbourhood is flanked by 26 Avenue SE while the western border is marked by 36 Street SE. The northern border is marked by 8 Avenue SE while parts of 48 Street SE and 52 Street SE occupy the eastern border.</p>
        <p class="par-lg">Forest Lawn also encompasses, apart from the current Forest Lawn neighbourhood, some portions of Albert Park or Radisson Heights and Southview that are located in the western part of the neighbourhood and parts of Forest Lawn Industrial and Penbrooke Meadows to the east.</p>
        <p class="par-lg">17 Avenue SE bisects the neighbourhood of Forest Lawn and is part of the Business Revitalization Zone.</p>
